#Text=RuPaul speaks about society and the state of drag as performance art
#Text=Saturday , October 6 , 2007
#Text=Few artists ever penetrate the subconscious level of American culture the way RuPaul Andre Charles did with the 1993 album Supermodel of the World .

#Text=It was groundbreaking not only because in the midst of the Grunge phenomenon did Charles have a dance hit on MTV , but because he did it as RuPaul , formerly known as Starbooty , a supermodel drag queen with a message : love everyone .
#Text=A duet with Elton John , an endorsement deal with MAC cosmetics , an eponymous talk show on VH-1 and roles in film propelled RuPaul into the new millennium .
#Text=In July , RuPaul 's movie Starrbooty began playing at film festivals and it is set to be released on DVD October 31st .
#Text=Wikinews reporter David Shankbone recently spoke with RuPaul by telephone in Los Angeles , where she is to appear on stage for DIVAS Simply Singing ! , a benefit for HIV-AIDS .
#Text=How are you doing ?
#Text=Everything is great .
#Text=I just settled into my new hotel room in downtown Los Angeles .
#Text=I have never stayed downtown , so I wanted to try it out .
#Text=L.A. is one of those traditional big cities where nobody goes downtown , but they are trying to change that .
#Text=How do you like Los Angeles ?
#Text=I love L.A.
#Text=I ’m from San Diego , and I lived here for six years .
#Text=It took me four years to fall in love with it and then those last two years I had fallen head over heels in love with it .
#Text=Where are you from ?
#Text=Me ?
#Text=I ’m from all over .
#Text=I have lived in 17 cities , six states and three countries .
#Text=Where were you when you were 15 ?
#Text=Georgia , in a small town at the bottom of Fulton County called Palmetto .
#Text=When I was in Georgia I went to South Fulton Technical School .
#Text=The last high school I ever went to was ...
#Text=actually , I do n’t remember the name of it .
#Text=Do you miss Atlanta ?
#Text=I miss the Atlanta that I lived in .
#Text=That Atlanta is long gone .
#Text=It ’s like a childhood friend who underwent head to toe plastic surgery and who I do n’t recognize anymore .
#Text=It ’s not that I do n’t like it ; I do like it .
#Text=It ’s just not the Atlanta that I grew up with .
#Text=It looks different because it went through that boomtown phase and so it has been transient .
#Text=What made Georgia Georgia to me is gone .
#Text=The last time I stayed in a hotel there my room was overlooking a construction site , and I realized the building that was torn down was a building that I had seen get built .
#Text=And it had been torn down to build a new building .
#Text=It was something you do n’t expect to see in your lifetime .
